page.title: 03F. OF DEAN NATURAL HISTORY
page.content: OUR CLASS OF 31 TEN & ELEVEN YEAR OLD PUPILS, IN GROUPS OF FIVE, ON A WALK THROUGH THE FOREST TO DECIDE THE LAND USE OF OUR DOMESDAY AREA, SAW THE FOLLOWING IN MAY: {TREES:}OAK, BEECH, SWEET CHESTNUT, PINE,SPRUCE,ASH,BIRCH, LARCH WILD CHERRY.{ANIMALS:}LAMB,SHEEP SQUIRREL, GRASS SNAKE, RABBITS, NEWT, BADGER,FOX & DEER PRINTS{FLOWERS}FUNGI JEWS EAR,COWSLIP, WILD VIOLETS, BLUEBELLS, CATKINS, LADIES SMOCK, FOXGLOVE, CELANDINE, WILD STRAWBERRIES GORSE, ROSE BAY WILLOW HERB. {BIRDS: MAGPIE, CHAFFINCH, KESTREL, JAY, ROOK, WOODPIGEON.{INSECTS:}MAYFLY,ANTS NESTS FLY, POND SKATER, LADYBIRD, BRIMSTONE, BEES, WASPS, YELLOWSPOT LADYBIRD, ORANGE TIP, SPIDER, CENTIPEDE, WOODLICE, WATER BOATMEN.
